        <type><ref refid="stdbool_8h_1abb452686968e48b67397da5f97445f5b" kindref="member">bool</ref></type>
        <definition>static bool atomic_test_bit</definition>
        <argsstring>(const atomic_t *target, int bit)</argsstring>
        <name>atomic_test_bit</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="atomic__types_8h_1a124f07c3a788e53c3a40e4e1c06d8af8" kindref="member">atomic_t</ref> *</type>
          <declname>target</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>bit</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Atomically get and test a bit. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Atomically get a value and then test whether bit number <emphasis>bit</emphasis> of <emphasis>target</emphasis> is set or not. The target may be a single atomic variable or an array of them.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>As for all atomic APIs, includes a full/sequentially-consistent memory barrier (where applicable).</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>target</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Address of atomic variable or array. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>bit</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Bit number (starting from 0).</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>true if the bit was set, false if it wasn&apos;t. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
